               AlphaD,Sega,Animaroid,PolygonPictures,LinksDigiWorks","created_time":"2009-01-17T16:01:47+00:00","account":"plus","pictures":[{"type":"portrait","width":30,"height":30,"link":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/portrait/1099083_30x30.jpg"},{"type":"portrait","width":75,"height":75,"link":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/portrait/1099083_75x75.jpg"},{"type":"portrait","width":100,"height":100,"link":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/portrait/1099083_100x100.jpg"},{"type":"portrait","width":300,"height":300,"link":"https://i.vimeocdn.com/portrait/1099083_300x300.jpg"}],"websites":[],"metadata":{"connections":{"activities":"/users/1172761/activities","albums":"/users/1172761/albums","channels":"/users/1172761/channels","feed":"/users/1172761/feed","followers":"/users/1172761/followers","following":"/users/1172761/following","groups":"/users/1172761/groups","likes":"/users/1172761/likes","portfolios":"/users/1172761/portfolios","videos":"/users/1172761/videos","shared":"/users/1172761/shared/videos","pictures":"/users/1172761/pictures","violations":null,"watchlater":null},"interactions":{"follow":{"added":false,"added_time":null,"uri":"/users/4443526/following/1172761"}}},"preferences":{"videos":{"privacy":null}},"stats":{}},{"uri":"/users/10932417","name":"FOO","link":"https://vimeo.com/whoisfoo","location":"Lleida","bio":"No doubts, there was no more time to waste in a university degree or in building an excellence CV, so in 2008 we made up our mind, forgot all the lessons from the catholic school, and gather to play good rock and roll, or maybe bad, the one coming in our heads, full of electricity and insanity.
So we end up in a kitchen, recording our first demo, cooking a bunch of irreverent songs, that in a completely nonsense way was calling us to move, to the search of some stage to play, to do something we know how to do, if there is anything. We were thirsty of rock, thirsty of the road. Where was our place inside the music world? We looked for it in small pubs, wrecking bars, we enter in some musical contests, but always were refused and ignored, like Yoko Ono.

MARC MOLAS, producer and the owner of ONARAMA RECORDS, a completely underground record company, was in the jury of one music contest where we were out. He wanted to know us, he showed us his studio, and we come in to record our first LP: ELENIN. First time we saw him it was a pretty hangover morning, he looked to as with his red eyes and dried mouth, everything smelling whiskey, in a recording studio that remembers a blend between raw and roasted: EL TOSTADERO.

We then started our parallel lives, guided by the wise of a music lover, who hold us with vinyls, amplifiers and a cat. In few weeks we isolated in the studio for preproduction and rehearsal, then the recording and finally a very long mixing process that left behind the “broken” sound of our demos and was looking for something even more broken of a young and fresh band. It was full of electric 90's sound, coming from British rock, it strengthened as musicians, we begun to see ourselves as a family and little by little we were finding our own sound, the perfect blend between dirt and valve.

Releasing the first album was an exiting experience, full of emotions, contradictions. Day after day we were in a metamorphosis, and we did our first tour in the “Península”. In the trip, traveling secondary roads and dusty ways, we rediscover our sound gig by gig, everytime we face ourselves playing in a small stage or in creepy pubs, in front on some Bukovski-looking crazy night junkheads. They could even intimidate us at the beginning of the show, but suddenly we get out the most “fuck” of our sound in each song. The show didn't end when the lights were off, it continued until the next gig in the next bar. And the road knows the tour could satisfy our thirst for rock. We take out our guitars in Madrid, Leon, Valencia, Monzon, Zaragoza, Barcelona, Terrasa, Lleida, Castelló, Pamplona, Vic, Torelló, Tarragona, and the list goes on and on...
We share onstage and something more with Peachy Joke, Pull my Strings, Julieta Jones and the begginings of Salvaje Montoya.  Elenin tour ended in a party at the art space “el Niu”, in Barcelona in the Poblenou heart.

Drunk after psychedelic experiences we wanted to close this forming time in a new single “THE RAIN”, with a b-side that again brought us back to touring Spain, finally our last stop was in Barcelona, this time with Wiggum in “sala Be Good”. We also show up in small festivals: Vall Sonora, LSD Festival, Harley Davidson Days. The Rain was released in digital format, and recorded totally live. Luckily we bring our live sound to the record, transforming it into some kind of rock with “garage” sound and psychedelic flashes, or that were the words of an old man who saw us in Tudela de Navarra, minutes before of telling his amazing tails in his young days playing the sitar.

Our new release, PARALLEL LIVES, captures the band metamorphosis, it's a music space where every sounding element has its place. It's been something unique, impossible to repeat, because it was recorded live in a factory in Gracia (Barcelona) neighborhood. This factory it's been transformed in a recording studio, to get an special ambient with lots of natural reverbs coming from industrial rooms, full of delays and 70's fuzz to squeeze your mind and your ears.
Kind of a mix between yesterday and today, and tomorrow as well, an spiritual essence has been captured into the tracks, building our own character and personality with all the work of this last 5 years devoted to music, rolling, flowing and dreaming to get the chance, or to die trying.
Back in production is again Marc Molas. This record has been made roughly in two days, the band playing together in “live” mode, to overcome our own limits another time, love and hate passions have been equally spread within us, but it is the only way to get our sound flowing.
This was born painfully, but with the smile in our face we burn the tires and the nights on the road, sleeping less, playing a lot, “drinkgym”, losing money, finding our dignity and at the end of the way the light, if it is there. A new tour in the spanish “Peninsula” will last from the end of the summer until the cold December.

This good boy, PARALLEL LIVES, will be released in a limited vinyl edition, for the posers, in a deserved homage to the years of authentic rock and in a digital release for the sons of the new era.
Tracks like Amazement or Savoir Faire will show a raw sound coming from improvisation and lots of awake hours. This record spans from typical 70s sound, a 90s personality, noise and ambients are interconnected and mixed with the most direct rock and finally the surf-rock flashes completely unseen. Sharp guitars and “c'mon” with the mouth half closed.
Heard the record, drink to glasses and heard it again to an insane volume. You will feel part of
